<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,223,248]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet 
<emphasis box="[569,644,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cheng &amp; Li &amp; Peng" authorityYear="2019" box="[574,644,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lesteva" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obesa">obesa</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
’ mean ‘obese’, referring to the morphology of the body in the male of the new species.
</paragraph>
